  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">WASH Unwrapped</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In Chirimanzu district, Oxfam is engaged in the third phase of a Research project which is  a continuation of the collaborative effort with Zvitambo where the tropical enteropathy, a subclinical condition where the human alimentary system gets impaired through ingestion of  micro -organisms that cause WASH related diseases. The study will examine the roles of nutrition and hygiene and sanitation in improving the growth of children from birth to 18 months of age. This project will co -fund the Research through the construction of 210 latrines and installation of 420 tippy taps.</narrative>
  </description>
